=== Verification (b): normal-path slug (all-lowercase, `epic-159-pillar-a2`
shape) unaffected ===

Driven end-to-end through `tests/lib/loop-driver.ps1`'s
`Invoke-DriveReviewRound -Stage spec` (which uses exactly this canonical
lowercase-hyphenated shape for every fixture feature slug it generates) --
see Verification (d) below: 27/0/0-SKIP in `loop-consistency.tests.ps1`
confirms every spec-review round drive still succeeds post-fix.
Additionally verified the `--reset` transition directly (not exercised by
either wave-1 suite): drove a clean round-1 PASS via
`Invoke-DriveReviewRound -Severity none`, then invoked
`spec-review-precheck.ps1 -Feature <slug> -Attempt 2 -Round 1 -Reset`
directly -- exit 0, `attempt-2/round-1/precheck-result.json` created, and
